a lot of kids would have gotten
hurt.

02:33.587 --> 02:36.957 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BLUE SANDEFUR, Parent: It didn't
inconvenience me, but I do think
that they overreacted.

02:36.957 --> 02:39.393 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I certainly think
they overreacted.

02:39.393 --> 02:42.763 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: New York City's
school system received a similar
threat, but it remained

02:42.763 --> 02:45.432 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
open.

02:45.432 --> 02:50.337 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Schools all over Pakistan closed
today, marking one year since a
Taliban attack that killed

02:50.337 --> 02:56.743 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
more than 140 people, nearly all
of them children. A special
ceremony in Peshawar began with

02:56.743 --> 03:02.749 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a moment of silence, honoring
those who died in the assault on
an army-run school. Prime

03:02.749 --> 03:08.055 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Minister Nawaz Sharif addressed
today's crowd and promised
vengeance on behalf of the
victims.

03:08.055 --> 03:14.428 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Yemen, a day-old cease-fire
appeared in peril, as continued
fighting killed at least

03:14.428 --> 03:21.101 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
42 people. Clashes broke out in
five provinces, including around
the besieged city of Taiz

03:21.101 --> 03:26.473 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Southwestern Yemen. Security
officials said shelling by
Houthi rebels killed six

03:26.473 --> 03:31.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
civilians. They said field
commanders and fighters from
both sides were ignoring
cease-fire

03:31.545 --> 03:36.616 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
