gathered in downtown Baltimore.

05:23.223 --> 05:26.826 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And Mayor Stephanie
Rawlings-Blake appealed for
calm.

05:26.826 --> 05:29.563 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MD-BO STEPHANIE RAWLINGS-BLAKE
(D), Mayor of Baltimore,
Maryland: Twelve Baltimore city

05:29.563 --> 05:36.570 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
residents answered the solemn
call to serve. They listened to
the evidence presented and

05:36.570 --> 05:43.777 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they rendered a decision. If
some choose to protest, they
must peacefully demonstrate.

05:43.777 --> 05:49.015 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is their right. But I also
want to be very, very clear
about any potential disturbances

05:49.015 --> 05:54.521 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in our city. We are
prepared to respond.

05:54.521 --> 05:59.626 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: William Porter was
the first of six officers to go
on trial in the case. In

05:59.626 --> 06:02.562 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a statement, Freddie Gray's
stepfather expressed confidence
in the proceedings, and he also

06:02.562 --> 06:04.864 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
urged calm.

06:04.864 --> 06:07.834 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RICHARD SHIPLEY, Freddie Gray's
Stepfather: We want to thank
this hardworking jury for

06:07.834 --> 06:12.739 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
