47:57.108 --> 48:08.586 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And finally tonight,
another in our series of essays,
a tradition here at

48:08.586 --> 48:10.654 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the "NewsHour."

48:10.654 --> 48:13.190 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Robin Givhan is the fashion
critic of The Washington Post
and the winner of the Pulitzer

48:13.190 --> 48:15.593 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Prize for Criticism.

48:15.593 --> 48:19.597 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tonight, she explores the sexism
behind some critiques of haute
couture.

48:19.597 --> 48:22.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBIN GIVHAN, Pulitzer Prize
Winner: Fashion makes people
nervous. Sometimes, they get

48:22.433 --> 48:25.636 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a little mean. They turn sexist.

48:25.636 --> 48:31.108 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I say fashion, I don't mean
basic T-shirts and jeans, or
even some scrim of a dress that

48:31.108 --> 48:34.245 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
leaves nothing to
the imagination.

48:34.245 --> 48:41.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean runway fashion, the
clothes that designers send out
on professional models, clothes
that

48:41.118 --> 48:45.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
speak to the state of our
culture, where it's moving and
how women and men will want to

48:45.689 --> 48:50.294 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be perceived in the public
square six months from now and
beyond.

48:50.294 --> 48:57.168 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For example, there is a movement
in fashion inspired by blurring
gender lines. A lot of

48:57.168 --> 49:01.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
designers have been part of this
conversation, but the most
aggressive has been Gucci's
Alessandro

49:01.939 --> 49:07.244 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Michele. He startled the fashion
industry with a men's wear
collection that included

49:07.244 --> 49:13.484 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ruffles, rows, and lace. Markers
of women's attire had been
applied to men. Here was social

49:13.484 --> 49:17.988 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
change meted out in the form
of a men's wear revolution.

49:17.988 --> 49:23.460 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dutch designer Iris van
Herpen merges fashion with
technology in the search for

49:23.460 --> 49:27.932 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
new materials and techniques.
Her clothes are otherworldly,
such as dresses that look

49:27.932 --> 49:30.634 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
like waves captured mid-splash.

49:30.634 --> 49:37.041 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's a futurist. And without
designers like her, we would all
still be in pantaloons and

49:37.041 --> 49:43.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hoopskirts. But when people see
her work, and Michele's, they
freak out. I know this

49:43.581 --> 49:49.186 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
because these people write to
me. It's only natural to be
unnerved by something that is

49:49.186 --> 49:53.324 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
unfamiliar, but other categories
of commerce regularly shock us,
without sending us into

49:53.324 --> 49:56.560 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a fit of aggrieved mocking.

49:56.560 --> 50:01.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For instance, we have been
informed that drones will soon
be delivering dog food to our
front

50:01.599 --> 50:07.404 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
door. And the only question we
ask is, how fast? In other
industries, tentative leap

50:07.404 --> 50:12.243 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
forwards encourage us to look
closer, but not fashion.

50:12.243 --> 50:18.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
With fashion, the first reaction
from so many, from so many men
in particular, is to laugh.

50:18.315 --> 50:24.321 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Who would wear that? If there is
one common thread in all this
lampooning and fretting,

50:24.321 --> 50:29.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it's the belief that the mere
existence of strange and
expensive fashion is an affront.

50:29.526 --> 50:35.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The fact that a woman might
spend $20,000 on a Dior haute
couture dress pushes many

50:35.733 --> 50:42.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people to distraction. They seem
to believe that the existence of
such an expensive garment

50:42.172 --> 50:49.546 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
endangers the existence of $100
ZARA dresses. I assure you the
$100 dress is safe.

50:49.546 --> 50:56.020 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I find this strange because I
don't detect similar outrage
over, say, fancy cars. We

50:56.020 --> 51:02.359 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
don't presume that the social
fabric is being shredded by your
$100,000 Cadillac or your

51:02.359 --> 51:07.264 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
$200,000 starter Bentley. But if
you build a special elevator for
them and then run for

51:07.264 --> 51:10.668 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
president, well, you
will have a problem.

51:10.668 --> 51:15.873 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The cultural conversation about
these luxury cars typically
centers on their engineering,

51:15.873 --> 51:22.146 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their sleek lines and their
precision. That same
conversation could be had about
fashion.

51:22.146 --> 51:26.250 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At its highest level, fashion is
also about proportions and
lines, balance and details,

51:26.250 --> 51:29.486 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and considering performance.

51:29.486 --> 51:35.259 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But the conversation is
different, because we still tend
to think of cars as boys' toys,

51:35.259 --> 51:40.965 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and fashion is for girls.
Fashion has a lot of problems of
its own making. It isn't as

51:40.965 --> 51:44.568 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
diverse as it should be. It
appeals to our insecurities. And
it struggles to balance

51:44.568 --> 51:48.372 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
creativity with commerce.

51:48.372 --> 51:53.510 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But it is pervasive and
influential, so we should
examine it seriously. It is
beautiful

51:53.510 --> 51:57.481 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and entertaining, too, and we
should enjoy that. We should
treat it no better and no

51:57.481 --> 52:00.718 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
worse than any other industry.

52:00.718 --> 52:06.223 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we dismiss it at our peril,
because, when men end up with a
closet full of floral lace

52:06.223 --> 52:13.197 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
shirts, they're going to want
to know how they got there.

